# Agent Discipline

Governance: `project-general.mdc`, repo root `AGENTS.md`. Multi-file workflow: `agent-multi-file.mdc`.

## Answer before you build

- Yes/no and advice → **direct answer in text first**, then code if needed
- Do not skip straight to implementation
- Do not refactor unrelated files while "helping"

## Next.js — docs before code

Training data is stale (Next.js `/docs/app/guides/ai-agents`). Before writing or changing `apps/app` behavior:

1. `nextjs-docs://llms-index` → `nextjs_docs` for the exact API
2. Do not guess App Router, cache, or Server Action behavior from memory
3. Runtime verification: `nextjs-mcp-quality.mdc` (stop hook runs `typecheck` when `apps/app` changes)

## Smallest layer (visual / UX)

| Order | Layer | Path |
|-------|-------|------|
| 1 | App wiring | `apps/app/` — `frontend-app.mdc` |
| 2 | Storybook | `apps/storybook/` — `frontend-storybook.mdc` |
| 3 | Design system | `packages/design-system/` — `frontend-design-system.mdc` — **ask before editing `components/ui/`** |

A layout or polish request is not permission to refactor shared primitives, tokens, or defaults.

## Do not repeat

- Changing shadcn primitives in `packages/design-system/components/ui/` for an app-only polish pass
- Editing `globals.css` token values to match one Storybook story
- `git restore` / `git checkout --` / `git clean` on untracked WIP unless explicitly asked

## When scope is wrong

Stop. Explain which layer fits. Ask: *"This requires changing `<file>` in the design system. Approve?"*
